<h3 id="2-project-structure">2. PROJECT STRUCTURE</h3>
<p><br />
<img src="/assets/img/QSB_project_structure.png" alt="prefab_describe" /></p>

<h3 id="setuppy">Setup.py</h3>
<p>Package and distribution managment placed at the root of repository, due to module package structure of the project.</p>

<h3 id="requirements-file">Requirements File</h3>
<p>A pip requirements file is placed at the root of repository. It specifies the dependencies required to contribute to the project: testing, building and generating documentation.</p>

<h3 id="modules">Modules</h3>
<p>Modules allows separating code into parts holding related data and functionality. The division allows to expand the functions, without the risk of breaking whole program.</p>

